@node "intro" "Introduction"


 INTRODUCTION 
         
    Mathan is a math tool for engineering students or mathematicians.
        
    Features:
        
    - 2D / 3D plots with rotations.
    - All scientific functions.
    - Engineering graphics like Bode, Nyquist or Root Locus plots.
    - Symbolic calculation.
    - Symbolic derivation (@{b}@{fg highlight}new V2.0@{ub}@{fg text}).
    - Numerical integration.
    - Complex numbers.
    - Complex roots of polynomials of any degree.
    - Matrices and matrix algebra ( LU / QR / eigenvalues...).
    - Linear simultaneous equation systems.
    - Exampes of Taylor and Fourier series.
    - ... and much more.
        
    If you hate reading docs and want to see a fast demonstration of
 Mathan try the next command from the shell (use the cursor keys to
 rotate and +/- to magnify the image):
 
        >mathan examples/demo.mth
@endnode

